## Test Suite

This project has a Vitest test suite (`pnpm test`). Tests live in `src/__tests__/`.

### Before Every Commit

1. Run `pnpm test` and confirm **all tests pass**.
2. If any test fails, **fix the root cause** (not the test) unless the test expectation is outdated.
3. If you changed business logic in any of these files, check whether existing tests still cover the change:
   - `src/utils/matryoshka.utils.ts` -> `matryoshka.utils.test.ts`
   - `src/utils/lockedPercentage.utils.ts` -> `lockedPercentage.utils.test.ts`
   - `src/utils/slots.utils.ts` -> `slots.utils.test.ts`
   - `src/services/PredictionService.ts` -> `predictionService.test.ts`
   - `src/domains/winner-selection/wheel-of-random/BaseWheel/helpers.ts` -> `wheelHelpers.test.ts`
   - `src/domains/auction/archive/lib/parsers/` -> `parsers.test.ts`
   - `src/domains/auction/archive/lib/validators.ts` -> `validators.test.ts`
   - `src/shared/lib/event-queue/` -> `eventQueue.test.ts`
   - `src/reducers/Slots/Slots.ts` -> `slotsReducer.test.ts`
4. If you added a **new pure function** or **new reducer action** that has non-trivial logic, add a test for it.

### When NOT to Write Tests

- Simple UI-only changes (styles, translations, layout).
- Generated code (`src/api/openapi/`).
- One-liner pass-through functions with no branching.

### Test Style

- Use `describe`/`it` from `vitest`. Globals are enabled.
- Import source via path aliases (`@utils/...`, `@models/...`, etc.).
- Test files go in `src/__tests__/<module>.test.ts`.
- Focus on edge cases: empty arrays, null/undefined, boundary values, -1 from findIndex.
